I""<p>One of my favourites backend frameworks is Ruby on Rails. Because is simple, is powderfull, and on version 6 you can add your Javascript dependencies using yarn. So, so excited about it.</p>

<p>These are the notes for adding Bootstrap to Rails project:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Type this on the console:</li>
</ol>

<pre>
<code>
yarn add bootstrap jquery popper.js
</code>
</pre>

<ol>
  <li>Your yourproject/config/webpack/environment.js file should look like this:</li>
</ol>

<pre>
<code>
const { environment } = require('@rails/webpacker')
const webpack = require('webpack')
environment.plugins.append("Provide", 
    new webpack.ProvidePlugin({
        $: 'jquery',
        jQuery: 'jquery',
        Popper: ['popper.js', 'default']
    })
)
module.exports = environment
</code>
</pre>

<ol>
  <li>Now we are going to import Bootstrap on app/javascript/packs/application.js with the following line:</li>
</ol>

<pre>
<code>
import "bootstrap"
</code>
</pre>

<ol>
  <li>On your gemfile you can add two gem more, for ‘bootstrap’ and ‘jquery-rails’, for my were these lines:</li>
</ol>

<pre>
<code>
gem 'bootstrap', '~&gt; 4.5', '&gt;= 4.5.2'
gem 'jquery-rails', '~&gt; 4.4'
</code>
</pre>

<p>I recommend go to https://rubygems.org/ and pick up the current versions.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Probably it’s a good idea to re-start your rails server:</li>
</ol>

<pre>
<code>
rails s
</code>
</pre>

